{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f510ac9a-228c-4568-8646-a06295c7d452","content":"I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory and `dotnet-dump` isn't installed yet. Here's what we can do:\n\n1. **Install `dotnet-dump`** — the primary tool for analyzing .NET crash dumps:\n   ```\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   ```\n\n2. **Analyze the dump** — once installed, open it with:\n   ```\n   dotnet-dump analyze /path/to/your/file.dmp\n   ```\n\n3. **Key commands** inside the analyzer:\n   | Command | Purpose |\n   |---|---|\n   | `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n   | `pe` (PrintException) | Show last exception details |\n   | `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n   | `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n   | `setthread <id>` then `clrstack` | Inspect other threads |\n\n**To get started**, copy or provide the path to your `.dmp` file and I'll install `dotnet-dump` and walk through the analysis with you interactively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a3c5c4b7-a912-485d-9564-ef4e7a0078b7","outputTokens":267,"requestId":"4189:3ED17A:5FB1DB4:690869A:69F16503"},"id":"7b715b97-f303-48ff-a1a1-991f73313b4d","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:55:22.418Z","parentId":"800bc4c6-5e10-4b55-a628-450b8b187dea"}
